desc.en: Brisbane is the third major city in Australia, its railway service is operated by the state government, QueenslandRail and Translink, extending south to Gold Coast, west to Ipswich/Rosewood and north to Sunshine Coast and Gympie. The gauge for its trains are 1067mm.

updateHistory.reason: This map is created and modified based on realistic geographical positions this map may look different to the official map
